44 (5) A resume that includes any trade learned by the inmate and such inmate's proficiency
45 at such trade;
46 (6) Documentation that the inmate has completed a practice job interview; and
47 (7) A notification to the inmate if he or she is eligible to apply for a license from a state
48 entity charged with oversight of an occupational license or certification.
49 (g) The following categories of inmates are not required to complete resumes or practice
50 job interviews prior to their release from incarceration:
51 (1) Inmates 65 years of age or older;
52 (2) Inmates releasing to medical reprieve or discharging from a prison infirmary setting;
53 (3) Inmates releasing to the custody of another jurisdiction on a warrant or detainer; and
54 (4) Inmates that the department determines would be physically or mentally unable to
55 return to the workforce upon release from incarceration.
56 (g)(h) The commissioner and other relevant state agencies shall be authorized to
57 promulgate rules and regulations necessary to carry out the provisions of this Code
58 section."
59 SECTION 2.
60 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
